{
  "text": "Control theory of networks and multiagent systems has gained enormous popularity in the last years, because it has numerous important applications [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] , and many unsolved mathematical questions. The dynamics of such networks are governed by the underlying topology (given by the edges of a graph) with predefined coupling rules and the dynamics of each agent at the nodes of the graph.",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "8368512",
